</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">ankur</dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 28 Feb 2016 16:52:27 +0000</pubDate><guid>tag:ankursinha.in,2016-02-28:/2016/02/28/new-zaphod-release-v0-5-7.html</guid><category>Research</category><category>LaTeX</category><category>Programming</category><category>Git</category><category>Fedora</category><category>Zaphod</category></item><item><title>Zaphod - a LaTeX change tracking tool</title><link>https://ankursinha.in/2016/02/13/zaphod-a-latex-change-tracking-tool.html</link><description>&lt;p class="first last"&gt;Introducing &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://github.com/sanjayankur31/zaphod"&gt;Zaphod&lt;/a&gt; - a &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://www.python.org/"&gt;Python&lt;/a&gt; script that attempts to help &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LaTeX"&gt;LaTeX&lt;/a&gt; users collaborate over their academic writing. It uses the power of &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Git_(software)"&gt;Git&lt;/a&gt; to track changes, &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://www.ctan.org/pkg/latexdiff?lang=en"&gt;latexdiff&lt;/a&gt; to generate a PDF with annotated additions and removals from the document, and provides a simple interactive review tool that lets the user pick what changes they want to accept. You can use Zaphod to track changes in your LaTeX documents.&lt;/p&gt;
</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">ankur</dc:creator><pubDate>Sat, 13 Feb 2016 17:16:24 +0000</pubDate><guid>tag:ankursinha.in,2016-02-13:/2016/02/13/zaphod-a-latex-change-tracking-tool.html</guid><category>Research</category><category>LaTeX</category><category>Programming</category><category>Git</category><category>Fedora</category><category>Zaphod</category></item></channel></rss>